timeline.bodyText:
This logic leads to false-positives when a test mix junit4 and junit5:
class JUnit4_5_mixed_but_compliant {
  @org.junit.Test void junit4() { }
  @org.junit.jupiter.api.Test void junit5() { }

  @org.junit.BeforeClass
  @org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeAll
  public static void setUp() { } // false-positive, please don't ask me to annotate this method with JUnit5 '@org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeAll' !!!

  @org.junit.AfterClass
  @org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterAll
  public void tearDown() { } // false-positive
}

